09/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two soldiers were killed and another was injured in southeast Turkey on Sunday (August 8th) by a land mine planted on a road in Mardin province.
Authorities suspect the remotely activated device was planted by the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
In another attack, PKK militants threw grenades at a police barracks in the Bitlis province, injuring one officer.
Separately, Turkish troops killed five PKK members during clashes in the southeast province of Batman late Sunday.
One of the rebels was a woman.
Two soldiers were injured.
(AFP - 09/08/10;
Reuters, AP, AFP, Anadolu news agency - 08/08/10)
